      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Synthesized hemolysis model accuracy evidence from prior published studies",
      "description": "This validation result consolidates findings from more than a dozen independent publications examining CFD-predicted hemolysis accuracy in rotary blood pumps, including centrifugal and axial configurations. The synthesis covers a range of operating conditions, blood analog fluids, and hemolysis power-law model variants. Collectively, the literature demonstrates that the power-law hemolysis model employed here achieves RH prediction errors within ±15% of experimental values when mesh resolution and turbulence closure are appropriately selected. The evidence base spans FDA-sponsored benchmark studies, peer-reviewed journal articles, and conference proceedings from 2008 through 2023, providing a comprehensive empirical foundation for the model accuracy claims in this COU.",
      "prov:wasDerivedFrom": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cpb-hemolysis-claim-cou1"
    },
    {
